# Business Context

QuickCart is a fictional e-commerce platform designed to provide customers with a seamless online shopping experience. Customers can browse products, place orders, make secure payments, and track deliveries through the platform.

As the business expanded across multiple cities and product categories, operational complexities increased, impacting customer experience and overall business performance.

The company began experiencing increasing order cancellations, delayed deliveries, inventory stock-outs, checkout abandonment, and declining customer retention. These issues resulted in reduced customer satisfaction and revenue loss.

Although operational data existed across different systems, business teams lacked a centralized view of key performance indicators, making it difficult to identify operational bottlenecks and take timely business decisions.

This case study aims to investigate these business challenges, identify their root causes, and propose practical business and technology solutions.

# Business Objectives

- Improve customer retention.
- Reduce order cancellation rate.
- Reduce stock-out rate.
- Improve delivery performance.
- Reduce checkout abandonment.
- Increase operational visibility.
- Enable data-driven decision making.
- Improve customer experience.

